§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬threshold graph❭ is an undirected graph for which there
    exists a real-valued function on the vertex set whose sum of
    results on two vertices is positive if and only if the
    vertices are adjacent in the graph. ⦉
⦉